snippet.textDisplay: You should really reconsider eating every animal in sight, as you normally do in your videos. As a person with a public platform you have a responsibility to be an agent of change for the better if you care about people and being a force for good. China culturally has a rather unfortunate reputation of killing and eating basically every animal that lives. This needs to stop, not only for the welfare of animals and to demonstrate some humanity, which we should be be demonstrating in 2020, but because raising and keeping hundreds of species of animals in close proximity to one another (as is regularly done in China) so that they can be later killed and consumed is what got us into this mess. COVID-19, like all corona viruses, jumped from animal to human, this could have potentially been avoided if the culture had some awareness of animal welfare and the science of animal habitats and nature as they were meant to be. We are not meant to raise, kill, and consume all animals. Logic, simple logic, if not compassion should change these activities.
